Offensive security is the process of breaking into computer systems, exploiting software bugs, and finding loopholes in applications to gain unauthorized access to them.
Defensive security, which is the process of protecting an organization's network and computer systems by analyzing and securing any potential digital threats.

First machine
-------------
GoBuster will take a list of potential page or directory names and tries accessing a website with each of them; if the page exists, it tells you.
CMD:gobuster -u http://fakebank.com/ -w wordlist.txt
